Nobody is going to crucify you for not wanting to put in some money to help care for a dog who you don't feel should be treated.  Not unless you come here and start spouting self-righteous or pro-euthanasia propoganda.<br>
<br>
If you don't have anything nice to say, don't say anything at all.<br>
<br>
With that in mind, inc donation, Ernie! <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#333333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub101.ezboard.com/uenzoblueksies.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Enzo Blueksies</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_bluespot.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Lurker</span><br>  Posts: 82<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(7/11/02 7:49:48 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub101.ezboard.com/fthetribunaldotorgfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1879.topic&index=30>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: If you own a lead pipe...</span><hr size=1> They should have put the dog down just because the pain must have been excrutiating.  This is a dog people, he's not thinking &quot;I wanna live so I can please human_01 an make the world a better place&quot;, he's thinking &quot; OW OW OW OW &quot; and extremely little beyond that.<br>
<br>
It's cruel to put the dog through months of excrutiatingly painful recovery procedures just so you can pat yourself on the back and say you saved a life.  It's for selfish reasons that we try.  He does not comprehend these procedures, he just knows that more humans are causeing him more pain.  If he lives and gets all healthy again, he's not gonna realize that the procedures saved his life, he's just gonna be happy the pain is over.<br>
<br>
After you can pamper the dog for the rest of it's life as if he deserved to be. He'll be forever grateful, but no more grateful that a healthy dog that is pampered.  Stopping the pain should be priority one when dealing with animals, because it's priority one for them. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#4D4D4D><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub101.ezboard.com/utelkandoretelenesis.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Telkandore Telenesis</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>I read boards more<br>than I play EQ....</span><br>  Posts: 568<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(7/11/02 8:43:06 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub101.ezboard.com/fthetribunaldotorgfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1879.topic&index=31>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: If you own a lead pipe...</span><hr size=1> Dogs as with all animals try to survive til the last minute. They rip themselves out of traps. They defend their young until death. They do not succumb to pain. I could very well argue that putting a dog to sleep is a selfish thing to do. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#333333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub101.ezboard.com/ucaledhontelrana.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Caledhon TelRana</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>l33t board camper</span><br>  Posts: 180<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(7/11/02 8:44:22 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub101.ezboard.com/fthetribunaldotorgfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1879.topic&index=32>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: If you own a lead pipe...</span><hr size=1> My wife used to raise and breed Shelties... she had neighbors climb over the tall wooden fence in her back yard, throw parties in her backyard pool while she was away, and slit her dogs mouths open with knives as side attractions.  One of them died because he couldn't even eat any more after that.  These people had their own dog too, which they mistreated so badly that my wife took pity on the thing and put food out for it because it was starving... it would have died otherwise.  People are disgusting...<br>
<br>
I'm not sure how kind keeping Daisy alive really is.  But that, to me, is not really an issue... if someone wants to shell out enough money to keep her going, power to them.  That's their decision.  I'm not sure I'd make the same one, but then, its their money.  They can do whatever they want with it - trying to preach at them about third world countries or whatnot is the most self righteous bullshit I've ever heard in my life.  I'll never understand why anyone would concern themself with how someone else they don't even know spends their own money.  That $12 you pay every month for Everquest could feed three starving Ethiopian families!!<br>
<br>
Its fine that you feel that way, Enzo, but not everyone would agree.  Animals cannot think past the moment, they live solely in the present and by instinct.  Pain exists to indicate to us that something is wrong, and we need to take care of it... pull your fingers away from the burning stove, or whatever.  Assuming the basic premise that every living thing in its right mind generally desires to keep living, while the animal would definitely want the pain to stop at that moment, the people involved, who care about the animal, can see past that moment unlike the dog... to a time when its healed and able to run around doing its happy doggy thing again.<br>
<br>
Anyway, the issue is more complex than you make it seem.  There are counter arguments to my argument too, but I think you get the general idea of what I'm trying to say. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#4D4D4D><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub101.ezboard.com/utelkandoretelenesis.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Telkandore Telenesis</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>I read boards more<br>than I play EQ....</span><br>  Posts: 569<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(7/11/02 8:55:55 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub101.ezboard.com/fthetribunaldotorgfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1879.topic&index=33>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: If you own a lead pipe...</span><hr size=1> Great minds something something something <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#333333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub101.ezboard.com/uenzoblueksies.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Enzo Blueksies</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_bluespot.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Lurker</span><br>  Posts: 84<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(7/11/02 9:36:11 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub101.ezboard.com/fthetribunaldotorgfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1879.topic&index=34>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: If you own a lead pipe...</span><hr size=1> I just hate to see animals in pain period.  Yes Telk, they do not succumb to pain but that's because they can't.  They have to endure it and will until they die.  It's instict.<br>
<br>
This is alot more complicated than it appears.  I guess it does boil down to a ratio of how much the animal means to you versus how much pain you'll make it endure.  And also how much foresight you'll do for the animal that's incapable of foresight.<br>
